# Docusaurus Structure

- Keep English content in `docs/` and Spanish content in `docs-es/`.
- When adding, renaming, or removing pages, check `sidebars.js` and `sidebars-es.js`.
- Preserve the repo’s frontmatter style on docs pages: `title`, `description`, `keywords`, and `image` where relevant.
- Keep site-level assumptions aligned with `docusaurus.config.js`, including `https://docs.zelf.world`, the `docs-es` plugin, and the existing search/navbar setup.
- Prefer working within the current doc taxonomy instead of inventing new top-level sections without a clear sidebar change.

## Examples

```md
---
title: Search Tag
description: Search Zelf tags by text query and retrieve matching entries with pagination.
keywords: [search zelf tag, zns search api, find zelf name]
image: /img/social-card.png
---
```
